block section_mouse_control 
  | Steady mouse control is important for Valorant, as duels are mainly won off of crosshair placement, reaction time and headshots
  | The chosen sensitivity can still widely differ, but it is important to end on a final sens that allows you to maintain consistent control of your mouse

block section_sensitivity 
  | Ideally the lowest possible sensitivity you should have is one that allows you to do a 180 turn across one swipe of your mousepad 
  | Anything slower than that makes large adjustments very hard and is not recommended
  | Your sensitivity should also take into account your mouse weight, with slower sens being more ideal for lighter mice, and higher sens for heavier ones 
  | In terms of average player sens for Valorant it falls somewhere between 0.24 - 0.5 800 DPI depending on factors such as mouse, character class, etc

block section_crosshair_placement
  | In order to improve your aim you must always focus on crosshair placement
  | At all times your crosshair should be placed at head level, while also pre-aiming potential places enemies can peek from 
  | This gives you a consistent advantage in all gun fights

